12. Implementation Notes for Worker A (Cloudflare Worker, ES module)
All identifiers (org_uuid, account_uuid, conv_uuid, message_uuid, tool_use_id, request_id, msg_id) generated via crypto.randomUUID() per-request, except for the canonical mimic identity which is read from KV / env.
request-id response header format: req_011 + crypto.randomUUID().replace(/-/g,'').slice(0,21).toUpperCase() (matches live shape).
msg_id format: msg_011 + 22-char base32.
toolu_id format: toolu_01 + 22-char base32.
Statsig response keys must be djb2-hashed strings (use the algorithm in §1.2).
Worker A never emits real Anthropic egress; all /v1/messages responses are either mock SSE or proxied through Worker C (which uses the operator's own browser session via credentials: 'include').
Cookie values MUST NOT appear in any Worker A code path; Worker C handles cookie-bridge mode entirely browser-side.
